\begin_layout Standard
A first question is to make sure that each consecutive sample of 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma$
\end_inset

 is uncorrelated with each other, which is impossible to determine directly
 because 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma$
\end_inset

 lies in a space with such a huge dimension; one pratical way is to examine
 the effect of any continuous function applied on 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma$
\end_inset

, such as 
\begin_inset Formula $H\left(\sigma\right)$
\end_inset

 or 
\begin_inset Formula $m\left(\sigma\right)$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Here we take an example when 
\begin_inset Formula $N=30$
\end_inset

