\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:p2_s1_act"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

.
 The samples will get more correlated when 
\begin_inset Formula $T$
\end_inset

 gets closer to the critical temperature, as the red line (
\begin_inset Formula $\beta=0.435$
\end_inset

) is much relaxed compared to the blue or yellow line (
\begin_inset Formula $\beta=0.48,0.4$
\end_inset

).
 So in general case, it is proper to skip a number of samples like 10000
 when the temperature is far from the critical, but that is not enough when
